            .well.project(data-toggle="gitorial-description")
              h3.reset.text-center#gitorial-logo gitorial
              // img.center-block(src="/public/images/texdown-logo-white-300.png")
    .project-expand#texdown-description
      .row.no-margin
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          h3 TeXDown 
            small - 
              a.brand-success(href="//www.texdown.org/") www.texdown.org
          p.lead For efficient Markdown note-taking infused with the power of LaTeX.
          p 
            | This is my favorite work-in-progress app. Targeting the technical CS/Math student, it allows people to efficiently combine the quickness and ease of Markdown note-taking with LaTeX for typesetting. It also features auto compilation, vim/emacs keybindings, cloud backup, and many other cool features that combine to make one awesome note-taking app. 
          p I'm honored to share this project with 
            a(href="http://oscarbezi.com/") Oscar Bezi
            | , who is a fellow student at Carnegie Mellon University. 
          a.brand-success(href="https://github.com/bezi/texdown") GitHub
    .project-expand#print-description
      .row.no-margin
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          h3 Print@ScottyLabs 
            small - 
              a.brand-success(href="//print.scottylabs.org/") print.scottylabs.org
          p.lead Send print jobs as attachments or through mobile interface send to a print queue.
          p This app is the collaborative result of 
            a(href="scottylabs.org") ScottyLabs
            | , a student organization dedicated to making things and helping fellow students make things. This project in particular has many plans for the future, including a mobile upload interface and more exhaustive printing features, to bring mobile printing at CMU up to the same level as desktop printing.
    .project-expand#gitorial-description
      .row.no-margin
        .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
          h3 gitorial 
            small - 
              a.brand-success(href="//www.gitorial.com/") www.gitorial.com
          p.lead With gitorial, making tutorials is as easy as commiting a repository to GitHub.
          p The product of TartanHacks 2014, this app won $750 worth of AWS credit and nearly placed overall. It reduces the process of creating a programming/code tutorial to three simple steps: make a GitHub repository where each commit is a step of a tutorial, sign in to gitorial to add some explanation text to each slide, and finally view your live tutorial.
          p This project never could have happened without the help of Aaron Gutierrez, 
            a(href="http://www.shyamr.info/") Shyam Raghavan
            | , and 
            a(href="http://westinlohne.com/") Westin Lohne
            | . In the future, we have tons of amazing features planned, the most prominent of which being using git diffs to show changes between steps, so people can more easily follow the sometimes subtle changes between steps of a tutorial.
          a.brand-success(href="https://github.com/shyamraghavan/gitorial") GitHub
    .row.no-margin
